description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infection Prevention and Control Support Nurse, AfC Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an Infection Prevention and Control Support Nurse to join an evolving Infection Prevention and Control team for Coventry and Warwickshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The new role  will be offered on a 2 year fixed term contract initially, on a full-time basis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as a member of the Infection Prevention and Control team in a developmental role, supervised by the Infection Prevention and Control Commissioning Nurses. You will be supported to promote, advocate and enable effective infection prevention and control practice through relationships with health and social care providers across Coventry and Warwickshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with the Local Authority, Public Health, Primary Care and Social Care providers, including care homes, to support quality assurance of community settings through:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the provision of infection prevention and control training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;surveillance of communicable infections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;auditing of environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;clinical practice audits You will be supported to escalate any infection control concerns which require specialist infection control advice or support to senior members of the Infection Prevention and Control team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you can demonstrate a passion for infection prevention and demonstrate transferable skills to a changing healthcare environment this could be the role for you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training will be given to successful applicants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date - 12/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date - 24/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sharon Stuart, Infection Prevention and Control Strategic Lead Nurse, sharon.stuart@southwarwickshireccg.nhs.uk or 07748 328692&lt;/p&gt;
